Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?phase9:=20wave=2013.6.2=20patch=200070=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20surface=20IRQ-1=20install-time=20+=20first-fire=20d?=
 =?UTF-8?q?iagnostics=20in=20DEBUG.LOG?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Pairs with SDL-side patch 0025 (which defines the new externs this
patch consumes). Wave 13.6.1 surfaced that IRQ-1 is silently
undelivered for ~42 s on PODP 5V83 real HW after main-loop entry, but
existing counters (kbd_irq_count, kbd_drain_count) can't discriminate
the four candidate causes from architect's
/tmp/wave-13-6-1-irq-mask-analysis.md §3. This patch adds five new
fields to the existing kbd/audio block N LOG_INFO line so a single
CF-card iter can answer:

  pump_pass        — current pump count (≈ flip count). Provides
                     scale for the *_ticks values below.
  pic1_mask        — inportb(0x21) snapshot at end of InitKeyboard.
                     Bit 1 (0x02) clear ⇒ IRQ-1 unmasked at the
                     controller. STATIC across blocks.
  first_irq_ticks  — pump_pass at first IRQ-1 fire (+1 encoding;
                     0 means "handler never fired").
  install_ticks    — pump_pass at end of InitKeyboard (always 0 in
                     practice; logged so the first_irq_ticks vs
                     install_ticks comparison is well-defined).
  vector_at_install — protected-mode IRQ-1 (.pm_offset) right after
                      DOS_HookInterrupt. Validates the chain wrapper
                      installed at the expected handler address.
                      STATIC across blocks.

Five extern declarations added to the existing extern "C" block at
namespace scope (matching patch 0068's linkage rationale: a plain
`extern volatile uint32_t foo;` inside the surrounding NXE::Graphics::
(anonymous namespace) would bind namespace-qualified and fail to link).
Qualifiers match the SDL-side definitions byte-for-byte; mismatched
qualifiers across TUs are UB.

pic1_irr (architect's §5b 5th field) is intentionally omitted for this
iter per team-lead direction — writing OCW3 (0x0A) to port 0x20 to
select IRR readback momentarily perturbs PIC state; pic1_mask alone is
enough to confirm/refute hypothesis 3a. If 3a is refuted, IRR can land
in a follow-up.

Adds 5 fields to the same line as the existing kbd_irq/kbd_drain/
ring_chunks. Per-block (every 100 flips) so cost is negligible.

Default behaviour unchanged — pure additive read-only diagnostic.

See architect's /tmp/wave-13-6-1-irq-mask-analysis.md §5b for spec,
§5c for the discrimination table.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 49 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 47 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index 34b59c4..c12a400 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -657,10 +657,23 @@ struct _DrawcallTimer
 // linkage spec is permitted at namespace scope in C++. Qualifiers MUST
 // match the SDL-side definitions byte-for-byte; mismatched qualifiers
 // across TUs are UB.
+//
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0070, Phase 9 wave 13.6.2): five new externs for the
+// IRQ-mask diagnostic log line. Same C-file defining TU as above; same
+// linkage rationale. doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count is logged alongside
+// the spec-required four fields so the engineer reading DEBUG.LOG can
+// localize first_irq_ticks against current pump-pass position (one
+// pump per flip) — without it, first_irq_ticks=N is a raw number with
+// no scale.
 extern "C" {
   extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_count;
   extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_drain_count;
   extern int doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active;
+  extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count;
+  extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_first_irq_ticks;
+  extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_install_ticks;
+  extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_vector_at_install;
+  extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_pic1_mask_at_install;
 }
 
 void _maybe_flush_phase_timing_audit()
@@ -722,11 +735,43 @@ void _maybe_flush_phase_timing_audit()
   // their comment block for the linkage rationale. The kbd counters
   // are MONOTONIC across the run (never reset) — read deltas between
   // consecutive blocks.
-  LOG_INFO("kbd/audio block {}: kbd_irq={} kbd_drain={} ring_chunks={}",
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0070, Phase 9 wave 13.6.2): extend the kbd/audio
+  // line with five IRQ-mask diagnostic fields. See architect's
+  // /tmp/wave-13-6-1-irq-mask-analysis.md §5b/§5c for the discrimination
+  // table. Format chosen so a single grep "kbd/audio block" tells the
+  // whole story per measurement run:
+  //   pump_pass        — current pump count (one per flip), gives scale
+  //                      for the *_ticks values below
+  //   pic1_mask        — inportb(0x21) snapshot at end of InitKeyboard.
+  //                      Bit 1 (0x02) clear => IRQ-1 unmasked at PIC.
+  //                      Static value (set once); same in every block.
+  //   first_irq_ticks  — pump_pass at first IRQ-1 fire (+1 encoding;
+  //                      0 means "handler never fired"). Compare to
+  //                      install_ticks and current pump_pass to localize
+  //                      the first fire in flip terms.
+  //   install_ticks    — pump_pass at end of InitKeyboard (always 0).
+  //                      Logged so first_irq_ticks vs install_ticks is
+  //                      well-defined.
+  //   vector_at_install— protected-mode IRQ-1 (.pm_offset) right after
+  //                      DOS_HookInterrupt. Validates chain wrapper
+  //                      installed at expected address. Static.
+  // pic1_irr (architect's §5b 5th field) is intentionally OMITTED for
+  // this iter per team-lead direction: writing OCW3 (0x0A) to port 0x20
+  // momentarily perturbs PIC state. pic1_mask alone suffices to confirm
+  // or refute hypothesis 3a; if 3a is refuted, IRR can be added in a
+  // follow-up patch.
+  LOG_INFO("kbd/audio block {}: kbd_irq={} kbd_drain={} ring_chunks={} "
+           "pump_pass={} pic1_mask=0x{:02x} first_irq_ticks={} "
+           "install_ticks={} vector_at_install=0x{:08x}",
            _dc_block_idx,
            (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_irq_count,
            (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_drain_count,
-           doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active);
+           doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active,
+           (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_pump_pass_count,
+           (unsigned)(doskutsu_kbd_pic1_mask_at_install & 0xff),
+           (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_first_irq_ticks,
+           (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_irq_install_ticks,
+           (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_irq_vector_at_install);
   _drawcall_accum_ns_block = 0;
   _drawcall_count_block = 0;
   _flip_inner_accum_ns_block = 0;
